    public class Node<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Node is a basic unit when it comes to data structures. It simply stores an element and references links to a next and a previous Node. This class uses Generics to allow the construction of Nodes storing any type of element. Nodes are building blocks which can be used to create LinkedLists, Stacks, Queues, Trees, etc. Virtually any data structure can be built out of Nodes.
